and decide on the PR/issue."}, {"id": 630652267, "node_id": "MDU6TGFiZWw2MzA2NTIyNjc=", "url": "https://api.github.com/repos/rust-lang/rust/labels/C-feature-request", "name": "C-feature-request", "color": "f5f1fd", "default": false, "description": "Category: A feature request, i.e: not implemented / a PR."}], "state": "closed", "locked": false, "assignee": null, "assignees": [], "milestone": null, "comments": 1, "created_at": "2020-02-24T18:21:27Z", "updated_at": "2021-12-20T15:03:18Z", "closed_at": "2021-12-20T15:03:18Z", "author_association": "CONTRIBUTOR", "active_lock_reason": null, "body": "~As far as I can tell, there's no good reason the `std` lib cannot~ It may be possible for the `std` lib to support `Clone` for `Box<T>` where `T: ?Sized`, although this requires nightly features. (I [implemented this for KAS](https://github.com/dhardy/kas/search?utf8=%E2%9C%93&q=CloneTo&type=) and leave the `std` implementation to someone else.)\r\n\r\n```rust\r\npub trait CloneTo {\r\n    unsafe fn clone_to(&self, out: *mut Self);\r\n}\r\n\r\nimpl<T: Clone + Sized> CloneTo for T {\r\n    unsafe fn clone_to(&self, out: *mut Self) {\r\n        let x = self.clone();\r\n        std::ptr::copy(&x, out, 1);\r\n        std::mem::forget(x);\r\n    }\r\n}\r\n\r\nimpl<T: Clone + ?Sized> Clone for Box<T> {\r\n    fn clone(&self) -> Self {\r\n        unsafe {\r\n            use crate::CloneTo;\r\n            let mut x = Box::new_uninit();\r\n            self.clone_to(x.as_mut_ptr());\r\n            x.assume_init()\r\n        }\r\n    }\r\n}\r\n```\r\nMore specific implementations: #25097 (`Box<[T]>`) and #27323 (`Box<str>`).", "closed_by": {"login": "dhardy", "id": 134893, "node_id": "MDQ6VXNlcjEzNDg5Mw==", "avatar_url": "https://avatars.githubusercontent.com/u/134893?v=4", "gravatar_id": "", "url": "https://api.github.com/users/dhardy", "html_url": "https://github.com/dhardy", "followers_url": "https://api.github.com/users/dhardy/followers", "following_url": "https://api.github.com/u